        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Use a repeater delay line (1 RT per row) to stagger the firing sequence precisely.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">06</span><span class="step-text">Closing sequence is reversed — outer rows retract first, then middle. Wire a second delay line for close signal.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">07</span><span class="step-text">Add a T-flip-flop so a single button controls open/close with appropriate delay before switching state.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Drawbridge -->
    <div class="tutorial-card">
      <div class="tutorial-tag-row">
        <span class="t-tag">PISTONS</span>
        <span class="t-tag">MOAT</span>
        <span class="t-tag">MEDIUM</span>
      </div>
      <span class="card-icon">🌉</span>
      <div class="card-title">Retractable Drawbridge</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A 4-wide bridge that retracts into the wall when powered — perfect for moats and castle gates.</div>
      <div class="step-flow">
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">01</span><span class="step-text">Build a 4-block wide gap (your moat). The bridge will span this gap when extended.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">02</span><span class="step-text">Place sticky pistons inside the wall facing outward across the gap, 4 wide and 1 tall.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">03</span><span class="step-text">Attach bridge blocks (stone slabs look great) to each piston head.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">04</span><span class="step-text">Wire all pistons together — power extends bridge, no power retracts it into the wall.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Use a lever inside your base to control — add a button outside that only extends (never retracts) for visitors.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Combo Lock -->
    <div class="tutorial-card">
      <div class="tutorial-tag-row">
        <span class="t-tag featured">SECURITY</span>
        <span class="t-tag">LOGIC</span>
        <span class="t-tag">HARD</span>
      </div>
      <span class="card-icon">🔓</span>
      <div class="card-title">4-Digit Combination Lock</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A sequential combination lock using 4 levers — must be toggled in the right order, not just the right positions.</div>
      <div class="step-flow">
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">01</span><span class="step-text">Place 4 levers labeled 1–4. Each lever press must happen in the specific sequence you set.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">02</span><span class="step-text">Build a T-flip-flop for each step that only engages when the previous step is complete.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">03</span><span class="step-text">Each flip-flop gate enables the NEXT lever's detection — wrong lever resets the entire chain.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">04</span><span class="step-text">Final flip-flop output triggers the door. Any incorrect press fires a reset pulse through all stages.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Add an alarm dispenser that activates on wrong input for anti-griefer protection.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Auto Sorter -->
    <div class="tutorial-card">
      <div class="tutorial-tag-row">
        <span class="t-tag featured">UTILITY</span>
        <span class="t-tag">HOPPERS</span>
        <span class="t-tag">MEDIUM</span>
      </div>
      <span class="card-icon">📦</span>
      <div class="card-title">Automatic Item Sorter</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A hopper-based sorting system that routes items into specific chests based on type.</div>
      <div class="step-flow">
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">01</span><span class="step-text">Build a main hopper line along the top of your chest wall — items flow horizontally through this trunk.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">02</span><span class="step-text">Place a hopper pointing into each chest you want to sort into. Connect it to the main line with a filter hopper above.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">03</span><span class="step-text">In each filter hopper, fill 4 slots with a non-target item (cobblestone) and leave 1 slot with the target item × 1.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">04</span><span class="step-text">Lock the filter hopper with a comparator + redstone signal so it only opens when target item passes through.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Items matching the filter drop into the chest below; unmatched items continue down the line to the next filter.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">06</span><span class="step-text">End the line with a misc chest for anything that doesn't match any filter category.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TNT Cannon -->
    <div class="tutorial-card">
      <div class="tutorial-tag-row">
        <span class="t-tag">EXPLOSIVES</span>
        <span class="t-tag">TNT</span>
        <span class="t-tag">MEDIUM</span>
      </div>
      <span class="card-icon">💣</span>
      <div class="card-title">TNT Cannon</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A water-cushioned TNT launcher using precise timing to fire a projectile TNT long distances.</div>
      <div class="step-flow">
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">01</span><span class="step-text">Dig a channel 7 blocks long, 1 wide, 1 deep. This is the cannon barrel.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">02</span><span class="step-text">Place water at the back end of the channel only — it absorbs the blast from propellant TNT.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">03</span><span class="step-text">Place 6 TNT along the channel (propellant). Place 1 TNT at the open front end (projectile).</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">04</span><span class="step-text">Wire a dispenser to drop the projectile TNT and simultaneously ignite propellant after a 1-tick delay.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Propellant explodes in water (no damage), shockwave launches projectile TNT forward at high speed.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Mob Farm -->
    <div class="tutorial-card">
      <div class="tutorial-tag-row">
        <span class="t-tag featured">FARM</span>
        <span class="t-tag">XP</span>
        <span class="t-tag">HARD</span>
      </div>
      <span class="card-icon">⚔️</span>
      <div class="card-title">Mob XP Farm</div>
      <div class="card-desc">A redstone-powered mob grinder with water flusher and drop shaft for AFK XP grinding.</div>
      <div class="step-flow">
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">01</span><span class="step-text">Build a 16×16 dark room platform 128+ blocks above your AFK spot (forces spawn here vs elsewhere).</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">02</span><span class="step-text">Add dispensers with water buckets on the outer walls on a 30-second clock to flush mobs to center.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">03</span><span class="step-text">Center has a 2×2 funnel leading to a drop shaft — mobs fall 22 blocks (leaves them at ½ heart).</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">04</span><span class="step-text">Place a hopper minecart below to collect drops, feeding into a sorted storage system.</span></div>
        <div class="step-row"><span class="step-num">05</span><span class="step-text">Stand at kill spot — one punch kills weakened mobs. AFK grind XP and loot efficiently.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- Scroll top -->
<div class="scroll-top" id="scrollTop" onclick="window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'})">▲</div>

<footer style="text-align:center; padding:40px 20px; color:var(--stone-light); font-family:'VT323',monospace; font-size:16px; letter-spacing:2px; border-top:1px solid var(--stone-mid); position:relative; z-index:1;">
  ◆ REDSTONE COMPENDIUM ◆ THE ADVANCED ENGINEER'S GUIDE ◆
</footer>

<script>
  // Particles
  const container = document.getElementById('particles');
  for (let i = 0; i < 18; i++) {
    const p = document.createElement('div');
    p.className = 'particle';
    p.style.left = Math.random() * 100 + '%';
    p.style.bottom = '0';
    p.style.setProperty('--dur', (2 + Math.random() * 3) + 's');
    p.style.setProperty('--delay', (Math.random() * 4) + 's');
    p.style.setProperty('--drift', (Math.random() * 60 - 30) + 'px');
    container.appendChild(p);
  }

  // Scroll progress
  const progress = document.getElementById('progress');
  const scrollTop = document.getElementById('scrollTop');
  window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    const pct = window.scrollY / (document.body.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight) * 100;
    progress.style.width = pct + '%';
    scrollTop.classList.toggle('visible', window.scrollY > 400);
    updateNav();
  });

  // Nav active state
  const sections = ['intro','easy','medium','hard','extreme','tutorials'];
  const navBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn');

  function updateNav() {
    let current = 'intro';
    sections.forEach(id => {
      const el = document.getElementById(id);
      if (el && window.scrollY >= el.offsetTop - 120) current = id;
    });
    navBtns.forEach((btn, i) => {
      btn.classList.toggle('active', sections[i] === current);
    });
  }

  function scrollTo(id) {
    const el = document.getElementById(id);
    if (el) el.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
  }

  // Card expand (click to expand steps on mobile)
  document.querySelectorAll('.card').forEach(card => {
    card.addEventListener('click', () => {
      card.style.gridColumn = card.style.gridColumn === 'span 2' ? '' : 'span 2';
    });
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
